meanings.definition: To project or extend outward beyond something else
meanings.sent1: The tree's branches jettiered over the fence.
meanings.sent2: The cat's tail jettiered out from behind the sofa.
meanings.sent3: The kite flew higher and higher, feeling jettier with each gust of wind.
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm for the project made her ideas jettier than anyone else's.
meanings.sent5: The rocket shot into the sky, reaching a jettier height than ever before.

meanings.definition: A structure built out into the water from a shore or bank
meanings.sent1: The fishermen gathered at the end of the jettier to catch fish.
meanings.sent2: Children love to jump off the jettier into the cool water below.
meanings.sent3: The seagulls perched on the jettier, waiting for scraps of food.
meanings.sent4: The old couple walked hand in hand along the jettier, enjoying the sea breeze.
meanings.sent5: The waves crashed against the jettier, creating a mesmerizing spray of water.
